<h2 id="why-the-context-on-a-website-is-important">Why the context on a website is important</h2>
<p>Page titles are essential to enable all users to quickly identify the content of a website. On the one hand, pages must be marked with the <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;title&gt;</code> element, so that pages in browser tabs can be quickly identified. On the other hand it makes sense to give each page a content describing <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;h1&gt;</code> title (main title), so that people with visual impairments or with memory weaknesses can put the pages into context faster.</p>

<p class="mb-8">Translated with www.DeepL.com/Translator (free version)</p>

